00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:22,231
you know, getting the hydrants color-coded, so that when the fire department goes out, they know right away how many hydrants they can hook up to, which ones they can hook up to, and they can put a fire out without, you know, hopefully faster than they can right now.

636
00:37:22,771 --> 00:37:28,476
You know, I mean, we have, I have so many plans for this department, but I mean, it costs money.

637
00:37:31,718 --> 00:37:32,478
Go ahead, please.

638
00:37:32,718 --> 00:37:35,739
Not all hydrants are accessible by the fire department?

639
00:37:35,859 --> 00:37:36,739
I didn't know that.

640
00:37:37,039 --> 00:37:39,099
So it's not that they're not accessible, right?

641
00:37:39,579 --> 00:37:53,642
What it is, is so as our water mains need to be replaced, what you have is like, say a dead end, for example, if you have a fire on a dead end, chances are that dead end is a six inch water main and it's 70 to 100 years old.

642
00:37:54,062 --> 00:37:57,982
So now the inside of the pipe is choked down to three inches.

643
00:37:58,603 --> 00:38:01,023
They go to hook up to that hydrant at the end of the dead end.

644
00:38:02,377 --> 00:38:03,798
and not getting much water out of that.

645
00:38:06,059 --> 00:38:11,241
But if they look, if we can, what we do is we fire flow each hydrant.

646
00:38:11,581 --> 00:38:15,883
We can calculate how much water we can gain from that hydrant.

647
00:38:16,323 --> 00:38:18,664
So they look at the dead end and it's painted red.

648
00:38:19,024 --> 00:38:20,444
That means they can't get much out of it.

649
00:38:20,825 --> 00:38:24,606
But they look just at the next road over and it's painted blue.

650
00:38:25,286 --> 00:38:29,128
Instead of wasting their time with that red hydrant, they're hopping on the blue one.

651
00:38:30,670 --> 00:38:33,035
And that could cost lives, yeah.

652
00:38:33,355 --> 00:38:35,699
It's good stuff, it's all good stuff.

653
00:38:35,719 --> 00:38:37,683
But it also costs money, you know.

654
00:38:38,004 --> 00:38:38,364
Of course.

655
00:38:39,472 --> 00:38:41,213
And that's not a great issue.

656
00:38:41,233 --> 00:38:45,574
