My gut is telling me as a resident from all my life and fourth generation here, I think this is a debt exclusion issue.

658
00:38:53,597 --> 00:39:05,961
And I think if the people in the city are informed that we're fifth oldest town in the United States, our piping system is old and it needs to be repaired.

659
00:39:07,316 --> 00:39:12,278
we need to make a vote on a ballot saying we've got to propose a 10 year plan and this is what we need.

660
00:39:12,318 --> 00:39:20,361
And we've got to pay more taxes, property tax, or we're going to make Flint, Michigan look like a sprinkler party.

661
00:39:20,681 --> 00:39:23,202
Flint, Michigan, Triah, Jackson, Mississippi.

662
00:39:23,502 --> 00:39:26,083
They can't supply water to their residents right now.

663
00:39:26,743 --> 00:39:29,124
Not able to.

664
00:39:29,204 --> 00:39:33,766
So what we can do as a commission going forward, and we'll try to have a meeting perhaps

665
00:39:35,223 --> 00:39:57,277
just the commission, well, whoever's gonna be the secretary, Ronnie and so on, to talk to the law department of the city of Manfred to see just exactly, given the bylaws that we have in terms of what we can and cannot do, if we can, above and beyond what the budget is, for example, I don't know, you got the new budget over here, whatever it is?

666
00:39:57,397 --> 00:39:59,518
It's not the budget, I don't have the budget.

667
00:40:03,583 --> 00:40:05,284
Yes, you are allowed to do that.

668
00:40:06,905 --> 00:40:12,547
Almost every other of my clients that I work with that does long-term financial planning takes that into consideration.

669
00:40:13,047 --> 00:40:19,090
They look at what their rates need to be in year 1 and also what they need to be in year 5 and potentially what they need to be in year 10.

670
00:40:19,830 --> 00:40:23,732
They do their best to smooth out the increases on an annual basis.

671
00:40:23,752 --> 00:40:26,993
You're not waiting until you get to say year 6 in a forecast,

672
00:40:27,433 --> 00:40:31,938
and you have to have a double-digit increase, it's better to have more programmatic increases annually.

673
00:40:32,459 --> 00:40:47,796
What gets built into the budget is a reserve fund contribution to slowly build up the rates over time, such that when you get to year 5 or year 10, your revenue is already built up to be able to support the revenue requirements or the total budget in that year.

674
00:40:48,457 --> 00:40:50,479
That's a incredibly common procedure.

675
00:40:51,820 --> 00:40:52,561
Yes, thank you.

676
00:40:52,661 --> 00:40:58,506
And I understand that, but we will need the law department to tell us in writing that that's exactly what we can do.

677
00:40:59,367 --> 00:41:04,672
